raw_data.title: BUSINESS INTEGRATION CONSULTANT
raw_data.description:
Possess at least 2 years of experience in information systems implementation, change management efforts or business process redesign.  A Business Integration Consultant applies their advanced skills and experience in systems development, possess detailed knowledge of business processes and has technical background and supervisory skills to implement business solutions. On projects, Business Integration Consultants provide direction to project teams and interact with clients at the supervisory level. A Business Integration Consultant is qualified to perform tasks such as: develop functional and technical information system designs, supervise business integration analysts in the development of software designs, computer programming, system testing or training curricula and lead business process redesign teams in the development of new business process architectures.
Also a Business Integration Consultant is responsible to design training programs for information systems users,  participate in quality reviews to ensure work complies with specified standards, and develop team workplans. In addition a Business Integration Consultant should perform workflow analyses, design and manage databases, define information system requirements and assist in project budget preparation.
